<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78a60011-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s383"><num value="383">§ 383.</num><heading> “Net income tax” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of this chapter, the term “net income tax” means any tax imposed on, or measured by, net income.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78a60012-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/86/272/tI/s103">Pub. L. 86–272, title I, § 103</ref>, <date date="1959-09-14">Sept. 14, 1959</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/73/556">73 Stat. 556</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
